description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Research Team are looking fora new colleague. If you are a Registered Nurse or Allied Health Professional and enjoy being part of an enthusiastic, dynamic multidisciplinary team delivering quality research projects to our patients, carers and staff, then this could be the job for you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role requires excellent communication skills, diligence, adaptability and a sense of humour. You will need to be a creative thinker, adapting to the ever changing research environments, specialities and diverse portfolio of projects. The role requires both team and independent working whilst adhering to Good Clinical Practice supporting a variety of National Institute for Health Research projects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in research desirable but training can be given to the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The position is for 22.5 hours a week over 3 days. We actively encourage calls to find out more about the position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date 11/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**As this post is in a shortage occupation code it qualifies for the Trust’s Recommend a Friend Scheme, please find further information on the attached link**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
